Now, let's remember that the **Net Present Value** $(\operatorname{NPV})$ of the merger is given by the following equation:

$$
\begin{equation}
\operatorname{NPV}=V^{*}_{B} -\text{Cost}_B
\end{equation}
$$

Where 

$V^{*}_{B}$ is the value of firm $B$ to firm $A$. This value is calculated by the sum of the **Market Value** of firm $B$ plus the **Synergy** value generated by the merger:

$$
\begin{equation}
V^{*}_{B}=V_{B}+\Delta V
\end{equation}
$$
